> So why are the Subaru engines so smoooth? Is there a balancer involved?

Horizontally opposed engines, by their very nature, are smooth and
don't require a harmonic balancer.

That being said, they do need to be in tune and healthy, otherwise it
won't matter HOW much vibration  damping you have.


